{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3ff05d77-d50f-45e1-9078-086242c60edb","content":"**Exit code 8** means \"fewer tests than expected were discovered.\" Microsoft.Testing.Platform defaults `--minimum-expected-tests` to **1**, so assemblies with zero tests fail — unlike VSTest which silently allowed it.\n\n**Fix:** Added `--minimum-expected-tests 0` via the `TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments` property in the `.csproj`. This tells the runner that discovering zero tests is acceptable.\n\n**Alternative approaches:**\n- Pass it at the CLI: `dotnet test -- --minimum-expected-tests 0`\n- Set it in a `Directory.Build.props` to apply across all test projects","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a362979e-0c01-434d-b809-0c779276875e","outputTokens":146,"requestId":"0432:225F33:1DB2D4A:218AAE7:69E81ACA"},"id":"8d70f026-ca9c-48ca-bca8-7840df2ca058","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:48:16.262Z","parentId":"a6c8c2dd-70e0-4567-a3bf-97eb80af90fe"}
